This paper deals with the security and privacy of smart home devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also presents a tool that uses machine learning techniques to detect specific device events, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the tool on various smart home devices, which can be considered as software engineering (cs.SE) research.
